parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the airbag is designed to cushion the impact and protect the occupants.
symptoms: Airbag did not deploy in a crash
despite meeting the deployment threshold; occupants sustained injuries or fatalities as a result.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, as the sudden deployment can distract the driver, cause loss of control, or deploy with excessive force.
symptoms: Airbag deployed without a crash or impact; airbag deployed with excessive force
causing damage to the vehicle or injuries to occupants; airbag deployed unexpectedly
causing loss of control or accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag system malfunction can lead to unintended airbag deployment, failure to deploy, or other unexpected behavior, which can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: causing unintended deployment or failure to deploy; airbag system malfunctioned

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the valve guide can cause engine misfires, hesitation, and stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the head gasket can cause engine coolant and oil leaks, leading to engine overheating, damage, and failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the crankshaft seal can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage, overheating, and failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Engine stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
The failure of the alternator can cause battery drain, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and electrical system failures, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Engine oil leaks can cause engine damage, overheating, and failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the computer sensor control unit can cause engine misfires, hesitation, and stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Engine failure can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents, injury, or death.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the front brake rotors and pads burn up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the brakes to become mushy, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, injury, or death.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, leading to accidents, injury, or death.
symptoms: The ABS brakes do not seem to slow or stop the vehicle quickly enough
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control and brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injury, or death.
symptoms: The cruise control stays on and cannot be canceled or turned off
the brakes go to the floor with no effect
the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down, leading to loss of power, stalling, and potential accidents.
